round and text colors, and button specifications for size and color. These are features the framework doesn't provide, so users would need to implement them separately.\n\nI'm also noticing the knowledge file is missing the \"未検討\" (not yet considered) section, which is important information for users to know what's explicitly out of scope.\n\nChecking the documentation against the source, the listbox display for code values is accurately described with the proper reference to the CodeManager documentation. The section structure shows 6 main headings in the source but only 3 in the knowledge file—though sections 4-6 are navigation-only so that's acceptable. The real issue is that the \"未検討\" subsection under the requirements section is missing from the knowledge file. I see the issue now—I was misreading the RST decorator hierarchy. The `----` underlines mark the h2-level sections, while the various `====` and shorter decorators beneath them indicate h3 and lower levels. So there are actually six main h2 sections: 概要, 特徴, 要求, カスタムタグライブラリの使用方法, タグリファレンス, and カスタムタグライブラリに関する設定, with subsections like 生産性の向上 and 画面設計の柔軟性 nested under 特徴, and status categories like 実装済み, 未実装, 未検討, and 取り下げ organized beneath those.\n\nThe real problem is that the \"未検討\" section—which documents 14 unsupported features—is completely missing from the knowledge file, even though it should be part of the 要求 section. This is a critical gap because an AI agent needs that information to accurately tell users what the framework doesn't support. The 未検討 section contains 14 items describing unsupported features—critical information an AI agent would need to know. The section title itself \"要求（実装済み・未実装・取り下げ）\" confirms this category is missing, and checking s1 more carefully, I notice the phrasing differs slightly from the source material, though the meaning is preserved.\n\nNow I'm verifying each section against the source: s1's constraints and HTML5 attributes all check out, s2's features around JSP sharing, client-side data handling, and double-submit prevention all match the documentation, and s3's implemented, unimplemented, and withdrawn items are all accounted for.\n\nThe only critical gap I'm finding is that the 未検討 (not yet examined) section is missing from the documentation. Looking at the V4 hints, they seem appropriate since the source doesn't contain PascalCase class names, annotations, or exception naming patterns that would trigger those checks.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20705,"cache_read_input_tokens":29873,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20705,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"01f5bae1-3808-411e-b81d-956a897d8615","uuid":"1ee7102c-cf42-429d-a2b3-90247862dcc6"}
